## The six tiers

Each paper is placed in the tier that best matches its contribution:

| Tier | Focus |
|---|---|
| **A** | **Boundary conditions** — inlet/outlet BCs, Windkessel, lumped parameter, fluid-structure coupling |
| **B** | **Turbulence & LES** — RANS, DES, LES, DNS applied to cardiovascular flows |
| **C** | **V&V and UQ** — grid convergence, uncertainty quantification, sensitivity analysis |
| **D** | **Physiology & scaling** — Murray's law, Windkessel theory, biomechanics |
| **E** | **Imaging & WSS** — 4D flow MRI, Doppler echo, WSS measurement techniques |
| **F** | **AI, ML & digital-twin pipelines** — PINN, neural operators, GNN surrogates, diffusion/transformer/foundation models, AI segmentation |

## How it works

The digest is built by [`paper_digest`](https://github.com/JieWangnk/aortacfd-agent/tree/main/paper_digest), a small module in the aortacfd-agent repo that:

1. Queries OpenAlex for papers published in the last 7 days matching cardiovascular CFD + AI keywords.
2. Queries arXiv for same-week preprints matching the same keyword set.
3. Deduplicates by DOI + title.
4. Asks Claude Haiku to score relevance (0–1), assign a tier, and write a 2-sentence summary.
5. Renders this page using a Jinja2 template.

The workflow runs on a GitHub Action cron every Monday at 09:00 UTC.

## Scope and limitations

We're explicit about what this digest does and does not try to do:

- **Abstract-level triage, not paper reading.** Claude Haiku reads the title and abstract — it does not read the full PDF. Summaries reflect what a paper *claims*; evaluate methods/limitations yourself before citing.
- **Published research only.** We deliberately exclude:
    - Industry product announcements (Siemens, Dassault, ANSYS, Philips blogs)
    - Non-indexed conference posters (some ASME / SC events)
    - GitHub releases of open-source CFD/ML code
    - Social-media discussion (Twitter/X, LinkedIn)
- **Anglophone bias.** OpenAlex and arXiv skew heavily toward English-language work.

For deeper analysis of a single paper, a direct chat with Claude (with the full PDF) will always go further than this digest. For industry and tooling news, follow vendor blogs and GitHub trending directly.

*Found something the digest missed? Open an [issue](https://github.com/JieWangnk/aortacfd-agent/issues) with the DOI.*
